1. *Leš* je pronađen u šumi. (*Leš* - The corpse was found in the forest.)
2. Videla sam *leš* pored puta. (I saw a corpse by the road.)
3. Hitna pomoć je prevezla *leš* u mrtvačnicu. (The ambulance transported the body to the mortuary.)
4. Policija je izvukla *leš* iz reke. (The police recovered the body from the river.)
5. Uznemirujuće je videti *leš* na ulici. (It's disturbing to see a corpse on the street.)
6. Lekar je utvrdio da je *leš* već neko vreme u vodi. (The doctor determined that the body had been in the water for some time.)
7. Porodica je identifikovala *leš* kao svog nestalog sina. (The family identified the body as their missing son.)
8. Forenzičari su pregledali *leš* kako bi utvrdili uzrok smrti. (Forensic investigators examined the body to determine the cause of death.)
9. *Leševi* su ležali rasuti po celoj sobi. (*Leševi* - Corpses were scattered throughout the room.)
10. U lokalnoj mrtvačnici nalaze se mnogi *leševi*. (The local mortuary contains many bodies.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "leš" can be either singular or plural, depending on the context. The singular form refers to one corpse, while the plural form "leševi" refers to multiple corpses.